      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><br>
        <b><font size="-1" color="#000000">PREPARATION</font></b><font color="#000000">:<font size="1"><br>
        <br>
        </font>Tribute Chai is best prepared according to the following method: 
        simmer 2-3 tsp. of spice per cup (8oz) of water 10-15 min. Remove from 
        heat and add 1-2 tsp. of tea to the pot and steep 5-10 min. (Add &frac12; 
        tsp. vanilla extract if desired.) While the tea and spices are steeping, 
        warm 1 cup soy (or other) milk in a separate pot. Strain the chai into 
        the milk, sweeten with honey (or sweetener of your choice) to taste and 
        serve. </font></font></p>
